Q1.
Write a code for basic HTML webpage with a heading, a paragraph, and an image image size should be 100px for both width and height.

Answer:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Webpage</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Welcome to the WebPage</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph part</p>
    <img src="imageroh.jpg" alt="ManImage">
  </body>
</html>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q2.
Wirte a HTML code with simple form with two input fields and a submit button.

Answer:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Login Page</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <form>
      <label for="email">Username:</label>
      <input type="email" id="email">
      <br>
      <label for="password">Password:</label>
      <input type="password" id="password">
      <br>
      <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>
  </body>
</html>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q3.
Create a HTML webpage with a table have three columns and three rows.Also style the table using css.

Answer:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Table</title>
    <style>
      table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      th, td {
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        padding: 8px;
        text-align: left;
      }

      th {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
      }
    </style>
     
  </head>
  <body>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Column 1</th>
        <th>Column 2</th>
        <th>Column 3</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Row 1, Column 1</td>
        <td>Row 1, Column 2</td>
        <td>Row 1, Column 3</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Row 2, Column 1</td>
        <td>Row 2, Column 2</td>
        <td>Row 2, Column 3</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Row 3, Column 1</td>
        <td>Row 3, Column 2</td>
        <td>Row 3, Column 3</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q4.
Add a dropdown menu with three options in HTML webpage.

Answer:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Dropdown Menu</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <label for="dropdown">Choose an option:</label>
    <select id="dropdown" name="dropdown">
      <option value="option1">Option 1</option>
      <option value="option2">Option 2</option>
      <option value="option3">Option 3</option>
    </select>
  </body>
</html>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q5.
Write a code for a hyperlink that opens a new tab when clicked.and define the size of content inside the anchor tag by css.

Answer:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Hyperlink</title>
    <style>
     a{
       font-size:20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Google</a>
  </body>
</html>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
